0. Requirements:

    0.1 - Java - OpenJDK (recommended, but all Sun-Compatible JVMs should work).
        >= Latest 1.6, 64-bit

    0.2 - Simple Build Tool (sbt: http://code.google.com/p/simple-build-tool/)
        >= 0.11

    0.3 - Scala (will be downloaded by sbt automatically)
        >= 2.9

    0.4 - ZSH Shell (for SvdSystemManager)
        >= 4.3.10

    0.5 - Sudo (for SvdSystemManager)
        >= 1.7.4p6

    0.6 - Smack library (for XMPP Notifications)
        >= 3.0.4

    0.7 - pIRCbot library (for IRC Notifications)
        >= 1.4.2

    0.8 - List of currently supported platforms:
        Mac OSX (100% features, development),
        Free BSD (100% features, production),



1. Instalation of software
    1.1 - bin/systemdeploy
    1.2 - Use "sofin" from https://github.com/dmilith/sofin


2. Testing
    2.1 - Use bin/sbt test

3. Custom sbt commands:
    cp        - show full classpath
    write-cp  - write classpaths to .classpath files

That's all folks



